The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Greek duo to face criminal inquiry
Athens: Greek sprinters Costas Kenteris and Katerina Thanou face a criminal investigation over missed drugs tests and a motorcycle accident, a judicial source said on Monday. The State Prosecutor Dimitris Papangelopoulos has ordered two prosecutors to officially investigate the incident involving the sprinters Costas Kenteris and Katerina Thanou. They will report the findings to him, the source said. The pair is set to leave hospital on Tuesday. A bulletin read to reporters outside the hospital on Monday afternoon said all medical tests had been completed, the pair was doing better and would be released on Tuesday. It said: Their clinical condition is improving and, provided it continues to develop satisfactorily, they will leave the hospital tomorrow. (Reuters)  Copyright 
